    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A thing or money, the use of which by another party is allowed for a time, on the understanding that it shall be returned or an equivalent given; often let out at interest, meaning payment must be made for the use of the thing or money.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
